\f0\b\fs52 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 Modular movie audio script for syncing\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 \
To ensure your stream runs continuously without the audio drifting out of sync with your on-screen "Now Playing" text, you need to track precise 
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 audio metrics
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 .\
Because your Python code loops through image names based on frames, and your audio plays back in seconds, a mismatch as tiny as a few milliseconds per song can add up over 24 hours. This results in the text displaying a new song title before the old song has actually finished playing.\
Here is the technical guide and script to calculate your audio metrics, configure your tracklist data, and generate your master audio loops with zero sync drift.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs42 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 1. Core Audio-to-Visual Metrics Checklist\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 Before building your playlist files, ensure your audio tracks are rendered using identical encoding settings. Mixing different bitrates or sample rates will cause FFmpeg to lose sync during long broadcasts.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f3\fs22 \AppleTypeServices \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f2\b\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Sample Rate:
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  Strictly 
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 44,100 Hz (44.1 kHz)
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 . This matches the standard YouTube streaming specification.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f3\fs22 \AppleTypeServices {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f2\b\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Bitrate Mode:
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  Strictly 
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Constant Bitrate (CBR)
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  at 
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 320 kbps
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  (or 192 kbps). Do 
\f4\i \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 not
\f1\i0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  use Variable Bitrate (VBR), as VBR files calculate time dynamically, causing your frame math to drift.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f3\fs22 \AppleTypeServices {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f2\b\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Channels:
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  Stereo.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f3\fs22 \AppleTypeServices {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f2\b\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 The Conversion Metric:
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  At 30 Frames Per Second (FPS), 
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 1 second of audio = exactly 30 frames of video
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 .\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0
\AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs42 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 2. Precise Automated Metric Analyzer Script\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 Instead of manually checking the length of dozens of songs using a media player, you can use Python to read your audio folder, extract the exact duration down to the millisecond, and automatically generate your 
\fs28\fsmilli14118 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 TRACKLIST
\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  data structure.\
First, install the lightweight audio metadata library via your terminal:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading40\partightenfactor0

\f5\fs28\fsmilli14118 \AppleTypeServices \cf0 pip install mutagen\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 Create a script named 
\fs28\fsmilli14118 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 generate_playlist_metrics.py
\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  and run it:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading40\partightenfactor0

\f5\fs28\fsmilli14118 \AppleTypeServices \cf0 import os\
import csv\
from mutagen.mp3 import MP3\
\
def analyze_audio_playlist(audio_folder="music_source"):\
    if not os.path.exists(audio_folder):\
        os.makedirs(audio_folder)\
        print(f"[INFO] Created '\{audio_folder\}/' directory. Place your raw MP3s inside it.")\
        return\
\
    print("=== ANALYZING PLAYLIST METRICS ===")\
    \
    total_seconds = 0.0\
    playlist_data = []\
    \
    
\f6\i # Sort files alphabetically to guarantee compilation order matches rendering order
\f5\i0 \
    mp3_files = sorted([f for f in os.listdir(audio_folder) if f.endswith(".mp3")])\
    \
    for file in mp3_files:\
        path = os.path.join(audio_folder, file)\
        \
        
\f6\i # Extract precise metadata headers
\f5\i0 \
        audio = MP3(path)\
        duration_in_seconds = audio.info.length\
        \
        
\f6\i # Extract metadata tags (Fallback to filename if tags are empty)
\f5\i0 \
        title = str(audio.get('TIT2', file.replace(".mp3", "")))\
        artist = str(audio.get('TPE1', "Unknown Producer"))\
        \
        
\f6\i # Calculate precise frame profiles at 30fps
\f5\i0 \
        exact_frames = duration_in_seconds * 30\
        \
        
\f6\i # Round cleanly to the nearest whole integer frame to prevent math drift
\f5\i0 \
        rounded_frames = round(exact_frames)\
        corrected_seconds = rounded_frames / 30\
        \
        playlist_data.append(\{\
            "filename": file,\
            "title": title,\
            "artist": artist,\
            "duration_sec": corrected_seconds,\
            "total_frames": rounded_frames\
        \})\
        \
        total_seconds += corrected_seconds\
        print(f"\uc0\u9989  Loaded: \{title\} | \{corrected_seconds:.3f\}s | \{rounded_frames\} Frames")\
\
    
\f6\i # Generate the exact Python dictionary code block to copy-paste
\f5\i0 \
    print("\\n=== COPY AND PASTE THIS INTO YOUR MAIN ENGINE ===")\
    print("TRACKLIST = [")\
    for track in playlist_data:\
        print(f'    \{\{"title": "\{track["title"]\}", "artist": "\{track["artist"]\}", "duration_sec": \{track["duration_sec"]\}\}\},')\
    print("]")\
    \
    
\f6\i # Generate the exact concatenation command for FFmpeg
\f5\i0 \
    print("\\n=== RUN THIS TERMINAL COMMAND TO CONCATENATE AUDIO ===")\
    concat_list = "|".join([os.path.join(audio_folder, t["filename"]) for t in playlist_data])\
    print(f'ffmpeg -i "concat:\{concat_list\}" -acodec copy lofi_music.mp3\\n')\
\
analyze_audio_playlist()\
