\f0\b\fs42 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 3. How the "Frame-Correction" Metric Works\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 Look closely at Phase 2 of the analysis script. An MP3 file might have a real-world length of 
\fs28\fsmilli14118 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 184.342
\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  seconds.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f3\fs22 \AppleTypeServices \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 At 30 FPS, that equals 5530.26 frames.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f3\fs22 \AppleTypeServices {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 A video engine cannot render a fraction of a frame (.26).\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f3\fs22 \AppleTypeServices {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 By rounding 5530.26 up to exactly 5530 frames, the script corrects the track duration to 184.333 seconds.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0
\AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 By forcing the tracklist array to use this corrected value, your text overlay will align perfectly with your audio track, remaining synchronized even after weeks of continuous broadcasting.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa80\partightenfactor0

